AddTags.name: AddTags
AddTags.description: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified Amazon SageMaker resource.

AssociateTrialComponent.name: AssociateTrialComponent
AssociateTrialComponent.description: Associate a trial component with a trial.

BatchGetMetrics.name: BatchGetMetrics
BatchGetMetrics.description:
Retrieve metrics associated with SageMaker Resources such as Training Jobs. This API
                                                is not publicly exposed at this point, however admins can control this action

BatchPutMetrics.name: BatchPutMetrics
BatchPutMetrics.description:
Publish metrics associated with a SageMaker Resource such as a Training Job. This
                                                API is not publicly exposed at this point, however admins can control this action

CreateApp.name: CreateApp
CreateApp.description: Grants permission to create an App for a SageMaker Studio UserProfile

CreateDomain.name: CreateDomain
CreateDomain.description: Grants permission to create a Domain for SageMaker Studio

CreateEndpoint.name: CreateEndpoint
CreateEndpoint.description: Creates an endpoint using the endpoint configuration specified in the request.

CreateEndpointConfig.name: CreateEndpointConfig
CreateEndpointConfig.description:
Creates an endpoint configuration that can be deployed using Amazon SageMaker hosting
                                                services.

CreateFlowDefinition.name: CreateFlowDefinition
CreateFlowDefinition.description: Creates a flow definition, which defines settings for a human workflow.

CreateHumanTaskUi.name: CreateHumanTaskUi
CreateHumanTaskUi.description: Defines the settings you will use for the human review workflow user interface.

CreateHyperParameterTuningJob.name: CreateHyperParameterTuningJob
CreateHyperParameterTuningJob.description: Creates hyper parameter tuning job that can be deployed using Amazon SageMaker.

CreateLabelingJob.name: CreateLabelingJob
CreateLabelingJob.description:
Starts a labeling job. A labeling job takes unlabeled data in and produces labeled
                                                data as output, which can be used for training SageMaker models.

CreateModel.name: CreateModel
CreateModel.description:
Creates a model in Amazon SageMaker. In the request, you specify a name for the model
                                                and describe one or more containers.

CreateNotebookInstance.name: CreateNotebookInstance
CreateNotebookInstance.description:
Creates an Amazon SageMaker notebook instance. A notebook instance is an Amazon EC2
                                                instance running on a Jupyter Notebook.

CreateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.name: CreateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
CreateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.description:
Creates an notebook instance lifecycle configuration that can be deployed using Amazon
                                                SageMaker.

CreatePresignedDomainUrl.name: CreatePresignedDomainUrl
CreatePresignedDomainUrl.description:
Grants permission to return a URL that you can use from your browser to connect to
                                                the Domain as a specified UserProfile when AuthMode is 'IAM'

CreatePresignedNotebookInstanceUrl.name: CreatePresignedNotebookInstanceUrl
CreatePresignedNotebookInstanceUrl.description: Returns a URL that you can use from your browser to connect to the Notebook Instance.

CreateProcessingJob.name: CreateProcessingJob
CreateProcessingJob.description:
Starts a processing job. After processing completes, Amazon SageMaker saves the resulting
                                                artifacts and other optional output to an Amazon S3 location that you specify.

CreateTrainingJob.name: CreateTrainingJob
CreateTrainingJob.description:
Starts a model training job. After training completes, Amazon SageMaker saves the
                                                resulting model artifacts and other optional output to an Amazon S3 location that
                                                you specify.

CreateTransformJob.name: CreateTransformJob
CreateTransformJob.description:
Starts a transform job. After the results are obtained, Amazon SageMaker saves them
                                                to an Amazon S3 location that you specify.

CreateUserProfile.name: CreateUserProfile
CreateUserProfile.description: Grants permission to create a UserProfile for a SageMaker Studio Domain

DeleteApp.name: DeleteApp
DeleteApp.description: Grants permission to delete an App

DeleteDomain.name: DeleteDomain
DeleteDomain.description: Grants permission to delete a Domain

DeleteEndpoint.name: DeleteEndpoint
DeleteEndpoint.description:
Deletes an endpoint. Amazon SageMaker frees up all the resources that were deployed
                                                when the endpoint was created.

DeleteEndpointConfig.name: DeleteEndpointConfig
DeleteEndpointConfig.description:
Deletes the endpoint configuration created using the CreateEndpointConfig API. The
                                                DeleteEndpointConfig API deletes only the specified configuration. It does not delete
                                                any endpoints created using the configuration.

DeleteModel.name: DeleteModel
DeleteModel.description:
Deletes a model created using the CreateModel API. The DeleteModel API deletes only
                                                the model entry in Amazon SageMaker that you created by calling the CreateModel API.
                                                It does not delete model artifacts, inference code, or the IAM role that you specified
                                                when creating the model.

DeleteMonitoringSchedule.name: DeleteMonitoringSchedule
DeleteMonitoringSchedule.description: Deletes a monitoring schedule. Amazon SageMaker will no longer run the scheduled monitoring.

DeleteNotebookInstance.name: DeleteNotebookInstance
DeleteNotebookInstance.description:
Deletes an Amazon SageMaker notebook instance. Before you can delete a notebook instance,
                                                you must call the StopNotebookInstance API.

DeleteNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.name: DeleteNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
DeleteNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.description:
Deletes an notebook instance lifecycle configuration that can be deployed using Amazon
                                                SageMaker.

DeleteTags.name: DeleteTags
DeleteTags.description: Deletes the specified set of tags from an Amazon SageMaker resource.

DeleteUserProfile.name: DeleteUserProfile
DeleteUserProfile.description: Grants permission to delete a UserProfile

DescribeApp.name: DescribeApp
DescribeApp.description: Grants permission to describe an App

DescribeAutoMLJob.name: DescribeAutoMLJob
DescribeAutoMLJob.description: Describes an automl job that was created via CreateAutoMLJob API.

DescribeCodeRepository.name: DescribeCodeRepository
DescribeCodeRepository.description: Returns information about a code repository.

DescribeCompilationJob.name: DescribeCompilationJob
DescribeCompilationJob.description: Returns information about a compilation job.

DescribeDomain.name: DescribeDomain
DescribeDomain.description: Grants permission to describe a Domain

DescribeEndpoint.name: DescribeEndpoint
DescribeEndpoint.description: Returns the description of an endpoint.

DescribeEndpointConfig.name: DescribeEndpointConfig
DescribeEndpointConfig.description:
Returns the description of an endpoint configuration, which was created using the
                                                CreateEndpointConfig API.

DescribeFlowDefinition.name: DescribeFlowDefinition
DescribeFlowDefinition.description: Returns detailed information about the specified flow definition.

DescribeHumanLoop.name: DescribeHumanLoop
DescribeHumanLoop.description: Returns detailed information about the specified human loop.

DescribeHumanTaskUi.name: DescribeHumanTaskUi
DescribeHumanTaskUi.description: Returns detailed information about the specified human review workflow user interface.

DescribeHyperParameterTuningJob.name: DescribeHyperParameterTuningJob
DescribeHyperParameterTuningJob.description:
Describes a hyper parameter tuning job that was created via CreateHyperParameterTuningJob
                                                API.

DescribeLabelingJob.name: DescribeLabelingJob
DescribeLabelingJob.description: Returns information about a labeling job.

DescribeModel.name: DescribeModel
DescribeModel.description: Describes a model that you created using the CreateModel API.

DescribeModelPackage.name: DescribeModelPackage
DescribeModelPackage.description: Returns information about a model package.

DescribeMonitoringSchedule.name: DescribeMonitoringSchedule
DescribeMonitoringSchedule.description: Returns information about a monitoring schedule.

DescribeNotebookInstance.name: DescribeNotebookInstance
DescribeNotebookInstance.description: Returns information about a notebook instance.

DescribeNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.name: DescribeNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
DescribeNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.description:
Describes an notebook instance lifecycle configuration that was created via CreateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
                                                API.

DescribeProcessingJob.name: DescribeProcessingJob
DescribeProcessingJob.description: Returns information about a processing job.

DescribeSubscribedWorkteam.name: DescribeSubscribedWorkteam
DescribeSubscribedWorkteam.description: Returns information about a subscribed workteam.

DescribeTrainingJob.name: DescribeTrainingJob
DescribeTrainingJob.description: Returns information about a training job.

DescribeTransformJob.name: DescribeTransformJob
DescribeTransformJob.description: Returns information about a transform job.

DescribeTrialComponent.name: DescribeTrialComponent
DescribeTrialComponent.description: Returns information about a trial component.

DescribeUserProfile.name: DescribeUserProfile
DescribeUserProfile.description: Grants permission to describe a UserProfile

DisassociateTrialComponent.name: DisassociateTrialComponent
DisassociateTrialComponent.description: Disassociate a trial component with a trial.

GetSearchSuggestions.name: GetSearchSuggestions
GetSearchSuggestions.description: Get search suggestions when provided with keyword.

InvokeEndpoint.name: InvokeEndpoint
InvokeEndpoint.description:
After you deploy a model into production using Amazon SageMaker hosting services,
                                                your client applications use this API to get inferences from the model hosted at the
                                                specified endpoint.

ListApps.name: ListApps
ListApps.description: Grants permission to list the Apps in your account

ListAutoMLJobs.name: ListAutoMLJobs
ListAutoMLJobs.description: Lists automl jobs created via the CreateAutoMLJob.

ListCandidatesForAutoMLJob.name: ListCandidatesForAutoMLJob
ListCandidatesForAutoMLJob.description: Lists candidates for automl job created via the CreateAutoMLJob.

ListDomains.name: ListDomains
ListDomains.description: Grants permission to list the Domains in your account

ListFlowDefinitions.name: ListFlowDefinitions
ListFlowDefinitions.description: Returns summary information about flow definitions, given the specified parameters.

ListHumanLoops.name: ListHumanLoops
ListHumanLoops.description: Returns summary information about human loops, given the specified parameters.

ListHumanTaskUis.name: ListHumanTaskUis
ListHumanTaskUis.description:
Returns summary information about human review workflow user interfaces, given the
                                                specified parameters.

ListHyperParameterTuningJobs.name: ListHyperParameterTuningJobs
ListHyperParameterTuningJobs.description: Lists hyper parameter tuning jobs that was created using Amazon SageMaker.

ListModels.name: ListModels
ListModels.description: Lists the models created with the CreateModel API.

ListNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfigs.name: ListNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfigs
ListNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfigs.description:
Lists notebook instance lifecycle configurations that can be deployed using Amazon
                                                SageMaker.

ListNotebookInstances.name: ListNotebookInstances
ListNotebookInstances.description:
Returns a list of the Amazon SageMaker notebook instances in the requester's account
                                                in an AWS Region.

ListTags.name: ListTags
ListTags.description: Returns the tag set associated with the specified resource.

ListTrainingJobsForHyperParameterTuningJ.name: ListTrainingJobsForHyperParameterTuningJob
ListTrainingJobsForHyperParameterTuningJ.description:
Lists training jobs for a hyper parameter tuning job that was created using Amazon
                                                SageMaker.

ListUserProfiles.name: ListUserProfiles
ListUserProfiles.description: Grants permission to list the UserProfiles in your account

RenderUiTemplate.name: RenderUiTemplate
RenderUiTemplate.description: Render a UI template used for a human annotation task.

StartNotebookInstance.name: StartNotebookInstance
StartNotebookInstance.description:
Launches an EC2 instance with the latest version of the libraries and attaches your
                                                EBS volume.

StopAutoMLJob.name: StopAutoMLJob
StopAutoMLJob.description: Stops a running automl job created via the CreateAutoMLJob.

StopHyperParameterTuningJob.name: StopHyperParameterTuningJob
StopHyperParameterTuningJob.description: Stops a running hyper parameter tuning job create via the CreateHyperParameterTuningJob.

StopLabelingJob.name: StopLabelingJob
StopLabelingJob.description: Stops a labeling job. Any labels already generated will be exported before stopping.

StopNotebookInstance.name: StopNotebookInstance
StopNotebookInstance.description:
Terminates the EC2 instance. Before terminating the instance, Amazon SageMaker disconnects
                                                the EBS volume from it. Amazon SageMaker preserves the EBS volume.

StopProcessingJob.name: StopProcessingJob
StopProcessingJob.description:
Stops a processing job. To stop a job, Amazon SageMaker sends the algorithm the SIGTERM
                                                signal, which delays job termination for 120 seconds.

StopTrainingJob.name: StopTrainingJob
StopTrainingJob.description:
Stops a training job. To stop a job, Amazon SageMaker sends the algorithm the SIGTERM
                                                signal, which delays job termination for 120 seconds.

StopTransformJob.name: StopTransformJob
StopTransformJob.description:
Stops a transform job.  When Amazon SageMaker receives a StopTransformJob request,
                                                the status of the job changes to Stopping.  After Amazon SageMaker stops the job,
                                                the status is set to Stopped

UpdateDomain.name: UpdateDomain
UpdateDomain.description: Grants permission to update a Domain

UpdateEndpoint.name: UpdateEndpoint
UpdateEndpoint.description: Updates an endpoint to use the endpoint configuration specified in the request.

UpdateEndpointWeightsAndCapacities.name: UpdateEndpointWeightsAndCapacities
UpdateEndpointWeightsAndCapacities.description:
Updates variant weight, capacity, or both of one or more variants associated with
                                                an endpoint.

UpdateNotebookInstance.name: UpdateNotebookInstance
UpdateNotebookInstance.description:
Updates a notebook instance. Notebook instance updates include upgrading or downgrading
                                                the EC2 instance used for your notebook instance to accommodate changes in your workload
                                                requirements. You can also update the VPC security groups.

UpdateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.name: UpdateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
UpdateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig.description:
Updates a notebook instance lifecycle configuration created with the CreateNotebookInstanceLifecycleConfig
                                                API.

UpdateUserProfile.name: UpdateUserProfile
UpdateUserProfile.description: Grants permission to update a UserProfile
